rComments: Professor Stump is the best. Took Environmental Ethics with him and learned so much. He's very energetic and approachable. Gives good feedback. He's sweet. I'd recommend him to everyone.

Jacob is an incredible & knowledgable teacher. I honestly think he is going to be one of the beat Philosophy professors I will ever take a course with during my undergrad years at uoft. Very respectable and Jacob is definitely on my top 5 favourite professors at uoft.

Jacob is a really spectacular professor. I had him in two courses at different levels and he was exceptional at tailoring the class to the level of the students but still challenging us. He's is very caring and easy to talk to and passionate about the material. I would likely have had no interest in this class and the content without him.

rComments: Professor Stump's Ethics class is amazing. He encourages students to think for themselves. He is open to different views, although he may challenge them stridently, but with respect. One of the best professor's. This is what university should be about, but often isn't.

The stump is a tremendous lecturer and human being. The representation of "she's" in his class is so inclusive, you would think he only believed in one gender. His music taste is impeccable and I could not stop tapping my toes, 3 hours a week. I love you Stump

Jacob is incredibly sharp, passionate, and knowledgable. He has a genuine love of the subject, and a love for teaching. If you ever have the chance, take his class! Get to know him. I cannot recommend Jacob enough, as an instructor and just as a person. Top 10 people I've ever met. My appreciation of his being is too great to fit in this word limi

One of the most enjoyable classes Ive taken at U of T. Prof. Stump presents the material clearly and is very open to discussion and argument about it. Some readings were difficult but overall really interesting and thought-provoking. This is what university is - encouraging us to think, question, develop and elucidate our ideas.

Prof Stump is a dream lecturer; down-to-earth, refreshingly informal, yet on-topic and (weirdly?) informative. Classes are engaging and discussion focused (for better or sometimes worse). He provided hands-down the most in-depth, useful grade feedback at u of t. However: marking was tough; my magnum opus barely broke an A. Still, I'd recommend it!

Jacob always shows great enthusiasm for teaching and is very passionate about helping students do their best. His lectures are organized and well-paced with lots of time for questions, comments, and class discussion. I received helpful feedback on my essays, and was very appreciative of all the time he took to help me strengthen my thesis.

Jacob is an excellent example of a young professor that understands the manner in which students learn. His lecture style made is such that information was presented in a clear fashion, and allowed plenty of time for questions throughout the lecture to clarify or consider any objection to course content (as any good philosophy class should do).

Stump is undoubtedly one of the most down to earth and fair professors I've had in my philosophy courses. That being said, he can be bipolar at times and he has relatively high expectations but if you work hard, you can surely get an A, even without a philosophy background. He's also very considerate about extensions. Overall, a great experience.
He was really engaging with the material and made class interesting! The assignments were also really interesting to do!!

He's a really good professor. If you go to his office hours, he will genuinely help you through with your ideas with great feedback. He grades very fairly -the more work you put in, the better grade you get. There are some pop quizzes but I believe those actually encouraged me to do readings more regularly which in return raise my overall grade.

Amazing, Amazing prof, he did a great job teaching a philosophy of emotions class, and given it was a survey course he did a good job! comical prof who really tests your ability too read, and very reasonable. pop quizzes were tough but in the end it turned out to be a grade saver if you attend his class.

rComments: Prof. Stump's a great professor. He's one of very few professors that actually want to see you succeed. He's very approachable during and outside of class, is extremely helpful, and explains theories or examples in a way that even non-philosophy students can understand. He makes the classroom environment really fun, as well.
- Fair and accomodating - Passionate and well versed in material - Creates an engaging classroom environment  - Jazz in the morning

Great instructor, knowledgeable and his interest in the topic shows through his teaching. Provided readings on portal for us. Does block off time for class participation. Also very understanding if you have conflicts of any type and replies to emails promptly

He is also super attractive!

rComments: Lectures were about readings which made it very easy to prepare for the exam. All slides were shared and Stump talked about the arguments of each author. He is pretty approachable in his office hours and he is enthusiastic. He takes his job and his students seriously. A great teacher. Due to his lectures, I would rate him 8.6/10.

rComments: Jacob is awesome!!! He is really knowledgeable about issues in Environmental Ethics, and his lectures are very clear and engaging.  His course inspired me to think in new ways about new ideas, and I found it SUPER helpful that he also took the time to teach us foundational skills for philosophical writing in general.  Would definitely recommend!
